Sure, here are some example sentences in Serbian that use the word "zdrav" in different forms and positions, along with their English translations:

1. Zdrav*e* seljak podigao je veliki usev. (Healthy farmer raised a large crop.)
2. Svakodnevno vežbanje čini čoveka zdrav*im*. (Daily exercise makes a person healthy.)
3. Doktor je rekao da imam zdrav*o* srce. (The doctor said I have a healthy heart.)
4. Potrebno je da jedemo zdrav*e* hrane da bismo ostali zdravi. (We need to eat healthy food to stay healthy.)
5. Zdrav*o* dete treba da ima dovoljno sna i redovnu ishranu. (A healthy child needs enough sleep and regular meals.)
6. Dobra ishrana ključna je za zdrav*e* življenje. (Good nutrition is key to a healthy life.)
7. On je jedan od najzdrav*ijih* ljudi koje poznajem. (He is one of the healthiest people I know.)
8. Lekar je propisao zdrav*e* životne navike kako bih se oporavio. (The doctor prescribed healthy habits for me to recover.)
9. Moja baka je živela dugo i zdrav*o*. (My grandmother lived long and healthy.)
10. Trebalo bi da pijemo dovoljno vode da bismo održali zdrav*u* hidrataciju. (We should drink enough water to maintain healthy hydration.)

Note: The word "zdrav" means "healthy" in English, and the star (*) indicates the stressed syllable of the word.